<HEADLINE> Surge Of Confidence Boosts UK's Beef Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Sales of British beef have hit
pre-BSE levels for the first time as confidence in its safety
increases.
</P>
<P>
According to a BBC report this afternoon, June figures were up
0.6 percent on sales for the same time two years ago.
</P>
<P>
It quoted the Meat and Livestock Commission as saying the
figures are the first to exceed 1995 levels and demonstrate "a
huge vote of confidence" by consumers.
</P>
<P>
BBC said that the Burger King and Mcdonald's to return to using
British beef has helped push up the figures. 
</P>
