<HEADLINE> Six Zimbabawean Projects Funded by U.S. Soft Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Southern African Enterprise
Development Fund (SAEDF ) has approved six job-creating projects
worth over 1.36 million U.S.Dollars in Zimbabwe under the country's
private sector development program, a SAEDF representative said here
today.
</P>
<P>
SAEDF's board member Strive Nasiyiwa said that funding had
been approved for projects in the financial services,
manufacturing and information technology sectors while a number
of other projects were still under consideration.
</P>
<P>
''We have approved between five and six major projects from
Zimbabwe which has now established itself as a key source of
projects for the fund,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
SAEDF is a 910 million U.S.Dollars soft loan facility
established by the U.S. government to support small-to-medium
scale enterprises in southern Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
