<HEADLINE> Hong Kong TV Maker Expands Manufacture in UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong television maker Onwa
Electronics is spending some 9 million US dollars on a program to
make its UK factory at South Shields, England.
</P>
<P>
A new production line, scheduled to be in place by November,
will make TV chassis rather than importing them from the Far East,
said the Invest in Britain Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Onwa will be able to manufacture some 500,000 sets a year. Its
parent company is Kong Wah Holdings, part of the Semi-Tech
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Max Schindele, managing director of Semi-Tech Europe, said,
"After this investment Onwa UK may be considered one of the most
modern TV factories in Europe."
</P>
<P>
"Sophisticated, high tech assembly lines will be installed to
meet the latest standard of television technology," Schindele
added. 
</P>
