<HEADLINE> Sinn Fein Calls for IRA Cease-Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Sinn Fein President Gerry Adams
today asked the Irish Republican Army (IRA) to restore a
cease-fire that collapsed in February 1996.
</P>
<P>
He made the call in a statement issued with the party's chief
negotiator Martin McGuinness in Dublin, the BBC reported.
</P>
<P>
Adams said they had been assured by the IRA that the
organization would respond without delay. Sinn Fein is the
political wing of the IRA.
