<P>
Earlier, Adams indicated in a joint statement with Northern
Ireland largest Catholic party leader John Hume that Britain had
removed some obstacles to meaningful negotiations on the future of
the province.
</P>
<P>
Britain and Ireland, who are partners in a three-year peace
initiative, say the IRA must abandon violence for Sinn Fein to be
given a place in all-party peace talks. 
