<HEADLINE> Cargo Traffic Down in Tanzania's Tanga Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Cargo traffic at Tanga
Port, north of here, has fallen by more than half the capacity
after the major factories in the region were closed down or
reduced their operation over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Talking at a workshop on privatization and commercialization
of Tanzania Harbors Authority (THA) held here today, Tanga Port
Manager Idi Mkwata said at the beginning of this decade the
maximum tonnage at Tanga Port was barely 130,000 tons compared to
500,000 tons per year in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The port manager disclosed that the number of ships anchored
at the port has declined from 10 to 6 ships per month.
</P>
<P>
He said the fall of production in some industrial sectors in
the region such as the Tanga Fertilizer Company, Tanga Steel
Rolls Company and Sigh Saw Mills which accounted for large
percentage of cargos at the port caused the decline on traffic in
Tanga.
</P>
<P>
So far Tanga Port has retrenched some of its workers in an
effort to reduce operation costs where human labor accounts for
more than 60 percent of the running costs.
</P>
<P>
Tanga Port is one of the Ports which are now under discussion
for the privatization exercise of the THA. Other ports are Dar es
Salaam and Mtwara ports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
