<HEADLINE> 14 Nuclear Safety Projects Completed in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Rosenergoatom Nuclear
Corporation completed 14 international projects worth nine million
US dollars to guarantee safety at Russian nuclear power stations
in the first half of 1997, the Interfax news agency reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was said that the corporation plans to draw a total of 50 to
55 million US dollars in foreign investments for the purpose this
year.
</P>
<P>
Interfax cited Anatoly Kirichenko, vice president of the
corporation, as saying the biggest grants decided on between
January-June were 44 million US dollars from the U.S. safety and
other programs. Moreover, Western countries are expected to offer
5-8 million US dollars under bilateral agreements.
</P>
<P>
Kirichenko said that a total of 25 nuclear safety projects are
to be carried out in Russia this year with Western funding.
</P>
<P>
The measures Rosenergoatom took to increase nuclear safety last
year were worth 54 million US dollars, when Western companies
delivered equipment worth 44 million US dollars and technologies
worth 10 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Kirichenko said this year under bilateral agreements France
decided on a 24.5 million US dollars quota for Russian nuclear
safety. The money will be allotted within 2-3 years. Besides,
several million dollars will be invested in the Russian energy
industry in five years in the framework of agreements with
Germany.
</P>
<P>
The United States is taking part in 46 Russian nuclear safety
projects worth 98 million US dollars and decided this year to
invest in 10 new ones worth 11 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
It is known that Rusenergoatom is currently involved in 12
international nuclear safety programs. In Russia 420 projects
worth 500 million US dollars are to be carried out in the
framework of these programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
