were present at the ceremony in the Old Executive Office Building.
Gore offered them his congratulations. "NASA has made our country
proud," he said.
</P>
<P>
Gore invited the group to get a closer look at the 14-foot by
three-foot photograph. The color picture, which shows a
reddish-brown, rocky terrain, will be displayed in the National
Air and Space Museum beginning next week. 
