<HEADLINE> Unemployment Drops in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's unemployment rate
in May stood at 16.1 percent, 1.2 percentage points lower than
that of last October, the National Statistics and Census Institute
(INDEC) said today.
</P>
<P>
The Buenos Aires province, the most populous province of the
country, registered an unemployment rate of 18.65 percent in the
month, less than 20.25 percent registered in October, 1996,
according to an INDEC study published today.
</P>
<P>
But, the jobless rate in the capital, Buenos Aires, increased
to 13.1 percent in May from 12.8 percent registered in October,
1996. 
</P>
