<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian President Stresses Importance of Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani today reiterated the importance of political parties
for Iran.
</P>
<P>
"I assert that for a serious electoral system, the presence of
parties is an undeniable necessity," Rafsanjani stated in an
interview with Persian daily Jomhuri Islami published today.
</P>
<P>
The out-going president has championed the cause of political
parties in Iran for the past two years. But the cause has
apparently encountered opposition from religious and political
groups, including Supreme Leader Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Husseini
Khamenei himself.
</P>
<P>
In a televized debate in November 1995, Rafsanjani expressed,
for the first time, his support for the formation of parties in
Iran.
</P>
<P>
In today's newspaper, Rafsanjani said "If there are parties
whose mottos, platforms and aims are defined and whose supporters
are known, then one can better predict the outcome" in an election.
</P>
<P>
In 1981, late Iranian Leader Khomeini issued an order to
dismantle political parties. There have been only political
factions and groups in the country since then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
