<HEADLINE> Bus Hijacker Overpowered by Passengers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A man, armed with a knife,
hijacked a bus in South Carolina today, but was overpowered by a
driver and some passengers and died about two hours later.
</P>
<P>
The man was "obviously unruly and he had been drinking" when he
boarded the bus carrying 25 passengers in Columbia, South
Carolina, shortly after midnight local time Friday,
Charlotte-Mecklenburg Police Capt. J.C. Felder said.
</P>
<P>
At one point, the man put a knife to the driver's throat and
removed the driver from the seat and took over as driver of the
bus, said Felder.
</P>
<P>
When the bus reached Charlotte on Interstate 77, the bus driver
managed to pull on the emergency brake, causing the hijacker to
lose control of the bus, which struck a concrete median and came
to a stop, said Felder.
</P>
<P>
Then some of the passengers jumped the man and fought on the
bus' steps and overpowered him.
</P>
<P>
When police arrived, they were unable to open the bus door, and
firefighters had to pry it open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
