<HEADLINE> Heavy Rainfall Eases Serious Drought In North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains that started yesterday
cooled the month-long heat-stroke in Beijing, and in Shaanxi,
Shanxi, Henan and Hebei provinces by this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The rainfall will help ease the serious drought that has
plagued the northern areas for the past month. It will of course
be good for the crops, say experts at the Central Meteorology
Station.
</P>
<P>
Precipitation since June has been reported to be 40 to 60
percent lower than normal for the same period in previous
years. More than 20 million hectares of farmland were affected as
of July 15.
</P>
<P>
The drought also struck a 670-kilometer area of the Yellow
River, which is also in the north, this summer.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists say that torrential rains will hit parts of
northern, northeastern, and central China in the next two to three
days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
