<HEADLINE> China's First Grads With Doctorate of Military Science </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- China's first group of students to
get a doctorate of military science graduated today from the
National Defence University.
</P>
<P>
The five graduates, two of whom majored in strategy, another
two in leadership, and the other in logistics, are all field grade
officers in the People's Liberation Army. They were assigned to
teach in major military universities in China after graduation.
</P>
<P>
Two hundred and forty-four officers have obtained master's
degrees at the university since it began accepting graduate
students of military science in 1987.  
