<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aid Worker Abducted in Mogadishu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, July 19 (Xinhua)-- A somali aid worker servig the
American non-govermental organization, CARE International, was
abducted by unidentified gunmen in North Mogadishu last night.
</P>
<P>
The abducted aid worker, Saed ADed Mohamed Firdhis, was
abducted by four gunmen near his house at Afarta Jardino junction
of North Mogadishu controlled by Ali Mahdi Mohamed.
</P>
<P>
According to local staff members of CARE International in
Mogadishu, Mohamed Firdhis has been the head of the Somali
Partnership Projects of CARE in Mogadishu where the agency handed
out several projects to other Somali NGOs to be implemented in
areas in Southern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The staff members said that Mohamed Firdhis has recently been
engaged in water wells and canals rehabilitation projects in the
Lower Shabelle, Lower Jubba and Middle Jubba regions in southern
Somalia as his main duty. Nevertheless, they did not relate the
abduction to his routine business and spoke about no problems
Mohamed Firdhis has had with other Somali people or NGOs.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the abduction is not yet known, however sources
close to the area where the abduction took place indicated that
the gunmen headed further to the North of the capital and would
most probably ask for huge ransom for his release.
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the headquarters of CARE International in
Mogadishu also said there's an undergoing mediation between the
abductors and Somali representatives of the agency. The agency
spoke about optimism that the undergoing mediation will bring
about a solution to end the captivity of Mohamed Firdhis soon.
</P>
<P>
The abduction of Mohamed Firdhis coincides with the arrival of
the strong religious leader, Sheikh Ali Sheikh Mohamud in North
Mogadishu yesterday afternoon. The religious leader, who was
welcomed by hundreds of cheering people and about 30 battle
wagons with heavily armed militiamen, has pledged his supporters
that the rule of the Sharia laws will be restored. He told his
supporters that the bandits will be dealt with severely.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Ali Sheikh Mohamud has been in Saudi Arabia for more
than two months after leaving Mogadishu following his armed
confromtations with the supporters of Ali Mahdi Nohamed in North
Mogadishu. He was relieved of his chairmanship of the Islamic
courts in a decree issued by Ali Mahdi in October last year, but
has been reinstated with mediation from the Abgal clan elders
which both Ali Mahdi and Sheikh Ali Sheikh Mohamud belong to.
</P>
<P>
Security in North Mogadishu has ever since been deteriorating
as too many gunmen and battle wagons wander in the streets with
no proper regulations to limit them. The people of North
Mogadishu are looking forward to what Sheikh Ali Sheikh Mohamud
will do about the current instability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
