<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Backing West China Petroleum Industry Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 19 (Xinhua) -- New technology has helped the
Changqing Oilfield in the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia Basin (Erdos
Basin), at the juncture of Shaanxi, Gansu and Shanxi provinces and
the Inner Mongolia and Ningxia Hui autonomous regions, find oil
and natural gas reserves and increase their output in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
The Changqing Petroleum Exploration Bureau has been carrying
out large-scale exploration and drilling in the
370,000-sq.km. basin, which is a major petroleum and gas producer
in northwest China, since the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
However, complicated ground conditions and the nature of the
oil-bearing strata have caused many difficulties in that work,
said Min Qi, president of the Changqing Exploration and
Development Institute.
</P>
<P>
"So scientific research and application of new technology are
always a major part of our exploration and production work," he
explained, attributing the increase in annual oil output from one
million tons several years ago to an expected 3.3 million tons
this year mainly to the unceasing development of new technology.
</P>
<P>
The use of seismic technology and geological research in the
past seven years have helped increase oil and gas reserves, Min
said, so that Changqing has 550 million tons of proven oil
reserves and 244 billion cu.m. of natural gas reserves, and has
the largest gasfield onshore China.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the century, it is expected to have more than one
billion tons of oil reserves and 500 billion cu.m. of gas
reserves, Min said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970719.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Backs Northwest China Oil Industry Development (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The research institute has successfully developed technology
for extracting oil from low permeability, low pressure oil strata,
which pose greater difficulties.
</P>
<P>
"The technology used to acidize and fracture the oil layer is
the most important step of production at the oil field," said Min,
noting that after it had some success in Changqing, the China
National Petroleum Corporation decided to adopt the technology
nationwide to develop four billion tons of oil deposited in these
layers.
</P>
<P>
At present, scientists make up about 20 percent of the
employees at the petroleum and gas complex, and more than 65
percent of their research results have been used in oil production.
</P>
<P>
Changqing has also begun co-operating with big foreign oil
companies and research institutes, as well as investing heavily in
imported facilities for research, Min said.
</P>
<P>
"By the end of the century, we will raise annual oil output to
over 4.5 million tons and annual gas production to three billion
cu.m.," he said. "Of course, new technology will continue to play
a leading role in meeting our goal." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
