<DOCNO> XIE19970719.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "People's Daily" Editorial Hails Inner Mongolia's 50th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- "People's Daily", a leading
Chinese newspaper and the organ of the Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee (CPC), will publish an editorial tomorrow to
mark the 50th anniversary of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The editorial starts by extending the congratulation and
greetings to the region's 23 million people, whose new system that
fits China's particular situation was created to solve ethnic
problems.
</P>
<P>
It says that in the past half century, under the leadership of
the CPC Central Committee, cadres and the general public in the
region have achieved a lot in the socialist revolution and
socialist construction. And remarkable changes have taken place in
the region.
</P>
<P>
The region is marked by political stability, economic
prosperity, ethnic unity, and social progress, the editorial says,
adding that those changes fully embody the superiority and
vitality of the regional autonomy system, which makes a great
contribution to the Marxist theory in ethnic policy.
</P>
<P>
The editorial says that while the whole nation is uniting
around the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at its core, the
people of Inner Mongolia should hold high the banner of Deng
Xiaoping to build socialism with Chinese characteristics to strive
for realizing the ambitious goals at the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
The editorial notes that economic construction is the nation's
main job, and so is that of ethnic autonomous regions. Some of
these autonomous regions, the editorial says, lag behind the
national average in economic development and therefore, they face
an especially pressing task in developing their economy to bridge
the gap between themselves and other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
"Regional autonomy system will mean nothing if the area cannot
achieve much in economic growth," the paper quotes Deng Xiaoping
as saying.
</P>
<P>
It calls for the sincere co-operation of Han Chinese and other
ethnic groups. The harmonious relationship must be cherished, and
the relationship of equality, unity, and mutual-assistance should
be further developed, the paper says.
</P>
<P>
The editorial concludes by saying that an even more prosperous
and thriving Inner Mongolia will be brought into the 21st century,
and the region will make a greater contribution to the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
