<HEADLINE> Government, Rebel Troops Traded Mortar Fires in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Philippine government troops and
Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rebels exchanged mortar fires
in Central Mindanao this morning despite a general ceasefire
signed by the two sides Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency reported that nobody was hurt in the
latest incident of mortar shelling, which occurred in two villages
in Buldon, Central Mindanao, around 04:00 today.
</P>
<P>
Noel Detoyato, spokesman for the government troops, said 12
mortar shells from the MILF landed near government army
detachments in Garigayan, while seven others exploded in Lagpan.
The two villages have been cleared of civilians, he said.
</P>
<P>
The enemy fires came from Tumaginting, also in Buldon, he said.
</P>
<P>
Detoyato said the incident occurred "maybe because the MILF
field commanders in Buldon do not know yet about the general
ceasefire agreement."
</P>
<P>
On Friday, representatives of the government and the MILF
signed the general ceasefire agreement that would take effect on
July 21.
</P>
<P>
The two parties will resume their peace talks on July 30, but
no venue has been decided yet.  
</P>
</TEXT>
