<HEADLINE> Conference On Inner Mongolia's 50th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A conference was held here today on
the 50th anniversary of the establishment of the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region, where China's regional autonomy system for
ethnic groups was first used.
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, Vice-premier and head of a central government
delegation, said at the gathering that the people of Inner
Mongolia have made a great contribution to the unity and
development of China.
</P>
<P>
"Over the past 50 years, they have had remarkable achievements
in socialist revolution and construction," Zou said.
</P>
<P>
Zou, who is a member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee reiterated that the central
government's policy of helping Inner Mongolia speed up development
will remain unchanged and that it will increase aid for the region
as central revenues increase.
</P>
<P>
The central government has decided to set up a three-million
yuan fund to award scientists in Inner Mongolia, he said, adding
that Inner Mongolia should increase economic development to
improve people's standard of living, make headway in the economic
reforms, open wider to the outside, and ensure ethnic unity and
social stability.
</P>
<P>
Liu Mingzu, secretary of the CPC Regional Committee of
Inner Mongolia, called on the 1,600 officials attending the
conference to concentrate on economic construction.  
</P>
