<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress, said today
that senior cultural relics experts are national treasures and
should be taken good care of by the government and by society.
</P>
<P>
Qiao made the remark at a symposium marking the 40th
anniversary of the establishment of the Cultural Relics Publishing
House, which has published some 3,000 different books, 769 issues
of magazines, and put out 10 different audio and video tapes on
cultural relics, archaeology, and museums since it was set up in
1957.
</P>
<P>
At least 130 of the books have won awards either at home or
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, State Councillor and a member of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee; Minister
of Culture Liu Zhongde; Director of State Bureau of Cultural
Relics Zhang Wenbin, and some 30 senior relics experts attended
the symposium. 
