<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaria Kills 176 Kenyans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- About 176 Kenyans have been
killed by malaria since the disease broke out in four districts
in the country late last month, the East African
Standard reported today.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims had taken too long to seek medical
treatment "and were only brought to health institutions when the
disease was too far gone," Nymira District Medical Officer of
Health Morris Obe said.
</P>
<P>
Children aged between six month and 10 years old are most
affected by the epidemic, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The situation was further worsened due to anemia and
malnutrition prevailing in the areas, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The four districts, located in western Kenya, are Kericho
where malaria claimed 70 lives, Uasin Gishu (67 dead), Nandi (21)
and Nyamira (12 ). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
