<DOCNO> XIE19970719.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IRA Announces Ceasefire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Irish Republican Army (IRA) has
announced a ceasefire from noon Sunday, Irish television company
RTE reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sinn Fein President Gerry Adams asked the IRA on Friday to
restore a ceasefire that collapsed in February 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sinn Fein is the political wing of the IRA which is an outlawed
guerrilla group fighting to end the British rule of Northern
Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The RTE said that the IRA announced in a statement it has
ordered "an unequivocal ceasefire." The IRA called for a truce in
August, 1994, but broke it in February 1996.
</P>
<P>
The IRA statement said that "all IRA units have been instructed
accordingly." 
</P>
</TEXT>
