<HEADLINE> Nigeria Agrees Warm-up With South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has agreed to let its Super
Eagles to play a warm-up match for 1998 World Cup with South
Africa's Bafana Bafana in October, a newspaper here reported on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's Tribune quoted an informed source as saying that the
sports ministry made the decision after being bombarded by a
series of invitation from the South Africa Football Association.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has emerged as one of the favorites to qualify for the
the World Cup finals in France after defeating Kenya 3-0 in a
qualifier on June 7.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian football body has received invitations from eight
countries for friendly matches by last week, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Danladi Bako, the spokesman of the Federal Ministry of Youth
and Sports, said earlier this week that a national team will be
formed by July 24 to ensure that Nigeria performs well in these
friendlies.
</P>
<P>
South Africa, who lifted the 1996 edition of the African
Nations Cup which Nigeria boycotted, has been eager to play
Nigeria so as to prove they are really the African best.
</P>
<P>
Bafana Bafana's head coach Clive Baker said during the week
that he was desperate for pitting his players against the Eagles.
</P>
