However, training of pilots in the college has been stopped since
1993, when a storm destroyed its 15 planes.
</P>
<P>
Since its inception in 1964, the college has reportedly
trained at least 4,200 aviation personnel, including pilots,
aircraft engineers and cabin-crews.  
