<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Technology Export Sees Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Technology export of this east
China metropolis retained a steady growth in the first half of
this years, as contracted earnings in foreign exchange surged 28
percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The earnings reached 320 million US dollars, compared with 250
million from January to June, 1996.
</P>
<P>
The catalog of high and new technology exports has been
expanded to cover more than 300 products, with more than 40 new
products. The earnings in foreign exchange from high-tech exports
rose 30 percent over the first half of last year.
</P>
<P>
Also growing has been the technology exports of non-state-owned
businesses, up 30 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
To expand the overseas market, scientific research institutes
and businesses in Shanghai have worked together in holding technology
fair overseas, inviting overseas businesses to attended fairs in
Shanghai, and cooperating with them to develop new and high
technologies.  
</P>
