<HEADLINE> OAU Urges Dialogues on Kenya's Constitutional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Secretary General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU), Salim Ahmed Salim, has
called for dialogue among Kenyan leaders in achieving solutions
of constitutional reforms, according to a East African Standard
report today.
</P>
<P>
The OAU boss made the remarks Friday during a stop-over
in Nairobi on his way from Mauritius. He said that Kenyan leaders
should accept President Daniel arap Moi's initiative of dialogue
towards the desired reforms.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Kenya had been renowed worldwide in terms of
peace, unity and stability and should not allow the recent events
to mar its name.
</P>
<P>
The OAU is definitely concerned about the violence in Kenya
witnessed during the past several weeks and urged Kenyan leaders
to cultivate a spirit of teamwork, Salim said.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan government and opposition leaders should initiate
meaningful dialogue to forestall further bloodshed in the East
African country. 
