<HEADLINE> Record Rainfall for July in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 19 (Xinhua) -- An accumulated 679 millimeters
of rain has fallen in Hong Kong since July 1, breaking the
centennial record kept by the local Observatory.
</P>
<P>
A trough of low pressure hanging over the South China coastal
waters has brought unsettled weather and continuous heavy rains to
the city since June this year.
</P>
<P>
The rainfall between July 1 and 18 hit 679 mm, exceeding the
historic high of 641.5 mm recorded in July 1886, reports the
114-year-old Hong Kong Observatory.
</P>
<P>
The Observatory forecast that thunderstorms and scattered
showers would continue to affect Hong Kong in the next few days.
</P>
</TEXT>
