<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Denmark has set aside about
24 million U.S. Dollars for the development of Tanzania's private
sector, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Birger Lorentzen, Counsellor of the Danish embassy here told
reporters that the fundig aimed to strengthen the private
sector's technical and financial base would be disbursed through
the Danish International Development Agency beginning from
October this year.
</P>
<P>
