<HEADLINE> Soeharto Calls for Open Economic System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
urged Asian and European countries to take advantage of the
world's economic openness to further enhance their people's
welfare.
</P>
<P>
"It is the responsibility of all nations to support the effort
to establish an open economic system and free trade by reducing
barriers to investment and free trade," the president said at a
state banquet he held last night to honor visiting Romanian
President Emil Constantinescu.
</P>
<P>
He said Europe was an important economic partner and a major
export destination for Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, we warmly welcome policies and strategies that
enhance the relations between the two regions," Soeharto said.
</P>
<P>
Asia-Europe cooperation was being pursued through the
Asia-Europe meeting (ASEM) which was held for the first time in
Bangkok, Thailand, in 1996 and would be held for the second time
in London, Britain, in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Referring to ASEAN, the president said all members of the
regional grouping had been working shoulder-to-shoulder to
establish mutual cooperation in the economic, social, cultural and
political fields.
</P>
<P>
"We are also trying to increase economic cooperation in the
Asia-Pacific region," Soeharto told Constantinescu who arrived
here Thursday for a three-day state visit.
</P>
<P>
On Friday morning, the two leaders held talks and agreed to
intensify the participation of the private sector to boost
bilateral trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
