<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Commemorates Martyrs' Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar held a state ceremony here
today to mark the 50th anniversary of the Martyrs' Day.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony, which took place at the Martyrs' Mausoleum in
commemoration of the passing away of the late Myanmar National
Independence Hero General Aung San and eight others, was attended
by Minister for Culture U Aung San on behalf of Chairman of the
Myanmar State Law and Order Restoration Council Senior-General
Than Shwe.
</P>
<P>
The late General's bereaved son U Aung San Oo and daughter Daw
Aung San Suu Kyi also took part in the ceremony, laying wreaths
and baskets of flower at the tombs.
</P>
<P>
50 years ago on July 19, 1947, the late General, along with his
eight Councilor Members, was assassinated in Yangon six months
before Myanmar regained independence from British colonialists.
</P>
