<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Marks 160th Birth Anniversary of National Hero </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria today marked the 160th
birth anniversary of Vassil Levski, leader and strategist of the
country's national liberation movement in the 19th century.
</P>
<P>
Devoting his whole life to Bulgaria's national liberation,
Levski had called on the people to fight against the Turkish rule.
</P>
<P>
He had said that the purpose of the movement was to "replace
the present despotic and tyrannical system by a democratic
republic."
</P>
<P>
Levski was convicted and executed in Sofia on February 19, 1873
by the Turkish authorities for his revolutionary activities.
</P>
<P>
