<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chilean Minister Praises Relations With Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Defense Minister Edmundo
Perez Yoma said today that the relationship between Chile and
Argentina has never been so good as it is now.
</P>
<P>
After a two-day meeting between the defense and foreign
ministers of the two countries, the two sides agreed to hold joint
military maneuvers in the first half of next year.
</P>
<P>
Yoma said that the good relations are the result of economic
integration, referring to the official association of Chile with
the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) starting in October 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean minister said that the agreement on joint military
maneuvers "is a historical event."
</P>
<P>
On the southern ice areas, the two governments reached an
agreement and submitted to their respective parliaments for
approval at the end of this year or the beginning of next year.
</P>
<P>
A border dispute in the southern ice fields has not been solved
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In 1991, Argentine President Carlos Menem and the then Chilean
president Patricio Aylwin reached an agreement that Argentina
would retain 2,238 square kilometers and Chile 1,057 square
kilometers of the areas, but the accord has not been officially
ratified. 
</P>
</TEXT>
