<HEADLINE> French Team Wins Foil Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- France captured its second
gold medal at the World Fencing Championships in Cape Town on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The French trio of Patrice L'Hotellier, Lionel Plumenail and
Franck Boidin overcame Cuba's foil team 45-43 in a gripping
final in which the lead changed hands three times.
</P>
<P>
L'Hotellier was France's hero, twice tilting the final back
to his side with 7-1 and 7-2 victories when his side trailed
15-13 and 35-33.
</P>
<P>
It was France's second gold after Erick Srecki's success in
the men's epee on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Italy won their second gold with a fine performance from their
women's foil team who recorded an ultimately comfortable 45-36
victory over Romania. 
